Well, they all did.

731
01:05:39,812 --> 01:05:43,482
And no one could figure out
why each kill was like a vendetta.

732
01:05:43,565 --> 01:05:46,610
You know, like it was really,
really personal.

733
01:05:46,693 --> 01:05:50,572
Because they filled my head with nightmares
and sent me on a suicide mission.

734
01:05:50,656 --> 01:05:52,116
Yeah, it certainly seems that way.

735
01:05:52,199 --> 01:05:56,203
I mean,
they've been clearly manipulating you.

736
01:05:56,286 --> 01:05:59,164
It's likely that what you think is real...

737
01:05:59,248 --> 01:06:00,916
sometimes ain't.

738
01:06:03,794 --> 01:06:05,712
Harting just used me.

739
01:06:07,297 --> 01:06:09,716
Just lied to my face over and over again.

740
01:06:09,800 --> 01:06:12,386
Yeah. He seems to be remarkably convincing.

741
01:06:12,469 --> 01:06:14,763
Told me my wife...

742
01:06:19,017 --> 01:06:20,394
Gina.

743
01:06:21,395 --> 01:06:23,522
I never even looked for her.

744
01:06:25,482 --> 01:06:27,734
But what if...?

745
01:06:29,820 --> 01:06:33,866
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Look, they're not gonna
just let you walk away.

746
01:06:33,949 --> 01:06:35,993
They'll come for you
and then they'll come for me too.

747
01:06:36,076 --> 01:06:39,496
- I'm looking forward to it.
- I'm not.

748
01:06:39,580 --> 01:06:41,790
Why do you think I went all biblical
and brought you back?

749
01:06:41,874 --> 01:06:45,377
You think I'm just running around here,
resurrecting people from the dead?

750
01:06:45,460 --> 01:06:46,962
If they plug you back in,

751
01:06:47,045 --> 01:06:50,966
it's going to be me in your head
killing that lovely wife of yours.

752
01:06:51,049 --> 01:06:53,468
And I've seen what you've done
to those people.

753
01:06:56,096 --> 01:06:57,806
Just gonna walk away from me, innit?

754
01:07:02,227 --> 01:07:05,439
My God, what are you...? What are you doing?

755
01:07:11,653 --> 01:07:13,363
You could figure out how these work.

756
01:07:14,364 --> 01:07:17,618
So just reverse-engineer
the work of dozens of scientists,

757
01:07:17,701 --> 01:07:20,412
billions of dollars
and a decade of genetic coding?

758
01:07:20,495 --> 01:07:22,581
Well, that's your superpower.

759
01:07:24,374 --> 01:07:27,336
I mean, yeah, I'll be done by dinner,
so it's not a big deal.

760
01:07:29,004 --> 01:07:31,757
That is absolutely amazing.

761
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:33,842
You know, I've heard the stories,

762
01:07:33,926 --> 01:07:37,471
but your entire system
is completely programmable.

763
01:07:37,554 --> 01:07:39,932
A program they no longer control.

764
01:07:42,601 --> 01:07:44,228
It's my army now.

765
01:07:45,354 --> 01:07:47,147
And your job to keep it that way.

766
01:07:49,650 --> 01:07:53,195
Okay. I believe the words
you were searching for were:

767
01:07:53,278 --> 01:07:54,988
[IN GRAVELLY VOICE]
"Thank you, Wigans.

768
01:07:55,072 --> 01:07:56,990
Thank you for resurrecting me
from the dead."

769
01:07:57,074 --> 01:07:59,493
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Oh, wait, I forgot.
I've got something for you.

770
01:07:59,576 --> 01:08:02,788
It should be right here
in my trusty lead-lined fridge.

771
01:08:02,871 --> 01:08:05,582
Oh, I am so clever. I don't want that.

772
01:08:05,666 --> 01:08:08,335
Right. Oh, here it is. Bingo.

773
01:08:10,254 --> 01:08:13,632
No! No! Not that one. That won't work.

774
01:08:13,715 --> 01:08:16,760
Trust me. Here, follow me. And take this.

775
01:08:16,843 --> 01:08:19,096
I don't need it.
The nanites will connect me to the Web.

776
01:08:19,179 --> 01:08:21,807
No, the nanites will connect you
to an RST server.

777
01:08:21,890 --> 01:08:25,185
They can track you that way, fill your head
with bullshit. You don't want that.

778
01:08:25,269 --> 01:08:28,772
Here, take it.
It'll connect you directly to a satellite.

779
01:08:28,855 --> 01:08:31,692
Vintage. No electronic parts.

780
01:08:31,775 --> 01:08:33,402
Thank you, Wigans.

781
01:08:46,248 --> 01:08:47,791
[ENGINE STARTS]

782
01:08:59,636 --> 01:09:01,346
[ALARM BEEPING]

783
01:09:01,430 --> 01:09:03,140
We've got movement.

784
01:09:05,267 --> 01:09:06,977
Is it him?

785
01:09:07,060 --> 01:09:08,437
I mean, it has to be.

786
01:09:08,520 --> 01:09:10,188
We still have no connection?

787
01:09:10,272 --> 01:09:14,151
ERIC: The network's still not responding.
- Okay, well, get Tibbs and Dalton there now.

788
01:09:18,030 --> 01:09:19,031
[DEVICE BEEPS]

789
01:09:19,114 --> 01:09:20,240
ERIC:
<i>You guys are a go.</i>

790
01:09:21,241 --> 01:09:22,284
Let's roll.

791
01:09:22,367 --> 01:09:27,247
<i>We've only got satellite tracking on him,
so reel him in fast before we lose visual.</i>

792
01:09:28,707 --> 01:09:31,626
- Now, remember, he's one of us.
- He was.

793
01:09:31,710 --> 01:09:32,836
[ENGINE STARTS]

794
01:09:32,919 --> 01:09:34,796
Now he's a problem.

795
01:09:38,633 --> 01:09:40,385
Relax.

796
01:09:40,469 --> 01:09:43,055
Now we finally get to use all this shit.

797
01:09:43,138 --> 01:09:45,432
[♪♪♪]

798
01:10:09,206 --> 01:10:10,457
[DOORBELL BUZZES]

799
01:10:14,920 --> 01:10:16,546
Ray?

800
01:10:18,632 --> 01:10:19,758
RAY:
Gina.

801
01:10:20,967 --> 01:10:23,804
What are you doing here? Hm?

802
01:10:24,513 --> 01:10:25,680
Hey.

803
01:10:26,681 --> 01:10:28,767
You'll never believe
what I just went through.

804
01:10:28,850 --> 01:10:32,646
Well, knowing you,
it's classified, huh? Heh.

805
01:10:32,729 --> 01:10:34,231
This has been crazy.

806
01:10:34,314 --> 01:10:35,774
I mean...

807
01:10:36,817 --> 01:10:38,235
I can't even...

808
01:10:39,694 --> 01:10:40,904
That doesn't matter.

809
01:10:43,740 --> 01:10:45,283
Because I'm home.

810
01:10:46,785 --> 01:10:47,661
Home?

811
01:10:51,623 --> 01:10:53,417
Yeah.

812
01:10:54,835 --> 01:10:56,169
I came back home.

813
01:10:57,295 --> 01:10:59,339
Ray, come on.

814
01:10:59,423 --> 01:11:01,007
I've moved on.

815
01:11:02,634 --> 01:11:05,470
Moved on? What are you talking about?

816
01:11:05,554 --> 01:11:07,222
We settled this.

817
01:11:07,305 --> 01:11:09,433
Ray, are you okay?

818
01:11:09,516 --> 01:11:11,476
What...? I mean, what's going on?

819
01:11:11,560 --> 01:11:15,480
I came home as I promised, didn't I?

820
01:11:15,564 --> 01:11:17,357
I always come home.

821
01:11:17,441 --> 01:11:20,610
Yes, I know,
but I didn't want you to come home.

822
01:11:20,694 --> 01:11:23,071
I wanted you to stay home.

823
01:11:23,155 --> 01:11:24,739
-Remember?
GIRL: Mommy.

824
01:11:29,161 --> 01:11:30,495
GINA:
Daisy.

825
01:11:31,663 --> 01:11:33,290
Daisy, go back inside, darling.

826
01:11:41,298 --> 01:11:43,508
Ray, I have a family now.

827
01:11:46,803 --> 01:11:49,014
When's the last time you saw me?

828
01:11:50,307 --> 01:11:54,102
I don't know. It's been a long time.

829
01:11:54,186 --> 01:11:56,146
When was it, Gina?

830
01:11:57,439 --> 01:11:58,732
Five years ago.

831
01:11:58,815 --> 01:12:01,276
Five years?

832
01:12:02,777 --> 01:12:04,905
DAISY: Mommy.
- One... One minute.

833
01:12:04,988 --> 01:12:07,199
- Are you okay, Ray? Can I...?
- Mommy, come and play.

834
01:12:07,282 --> 01:12:09,576
One... Can I call someone?

835
01:12:09,659 --> 01:12:11,620
- Mommy!
- Ray...

836
01:12:11,703 --> 01:12:13,955
Daisy, go and play with your brother.
Good girl.

837
01:12:14,039 --> 01:12:15,999
Go find Daddy.

838
01:12:18,752 --> 01:12:21,254
[♪♪♪]

839
01:12:28,637 --> 01:12:32,599
GINA: <i>You think someday you could come back
in the same shape you left?</i>

840
01:12:34,893 --> 01:12:37,562
RAY: <i>Because they all end the same.</i>
GINA: <i>Ray.</i>

841
01:12:37,646 --> 01:12:39,731
RAY: <i>I always come home.</i>
GINA: <i>Ray.</i>

842
01:12:58,917 --> 01:13:01,336
DALTON:
How's that shit feel, old man, huh?

843
01:13:21,648 --> 01:13:24,526
- Tibbs! Get a tracker on him!
- Coming up.

844
01:13:36,746 --> 01:13:38,123
Eyes are in the sky.

845
01:13:47,132 --> 01:13:48,717
There he is.

846
01:13:50,343 --> 01:13:51,386
On my way.

847
01:14:08,570 --> 01:14:10,614
DALTON:
Tibbs! I can't see him!

848
01:14:13,366 --> 01:14:15,660
TIBBS:
<i>On the run, two blocks west.</i>

849
01:14:35,138 --> 01:14:37,474
[♪♪♪]

850
01:14:43,063 --> 01:14:45,190
[PATRONS SCREAMING]

851
01:14:48,693 --> 01:14:51,154
- Hey, whoa, whoa, mate! Hey.
- Get back!

852
01:14:51,237 --> 01:14:52,405
Hey!

853
01:14:56,576 --> 01:14:58,578
[BOTH YELLING]

854
01:15:02,582 --> 01:15:04,334
You're kidding me!

855
01:15:04,417 --> 01:15:05,377
What the...?

856
01:15:14,761 --> 01:15:16,179
[GASPING]

857
01:15:17,597 --> 01:15:19,265
TIBBS:
<i>I've still got him, Dalton. Head south.</i>

858
01:15:19,349 --> 01:15:20,517
DALTON:
<i>South?</i>

859
01:15:20,600 --> 01:15:22,769
- Jesus, man, right or left?
- Left.

860
01:15:23,937 --> 01:15:27,107
<i>Left again. Move, move!
You'll get him at the corner.</i>

861
01:15:35,031 --> 01:15:36,324
TIBBS:
Dalton, look out!

862
01:15:36,408 --> 01:15:38,410
Come on! Stop!

863
01:15:42,747 --> 01:15:43,665
[YELPS]

864
01:15:46,793 --> 01:15:50,422
MAN: Oh, bloody hell, mate. You okay?
Oh, I'm not sure you should be getting up.

865
01:15:50,505 --> 01:15:52,298
Maybe we can...

866
01:15:55,927 --> 01:15:57,220
Shit.

867
01:15:57,303 --> 01:15:59,180
[DALTON GROANING]

868
01:16:12,902 --> 01:16:14,946
TIBBS:
Tagged him. Jackknives are in.

869
01:16:15,029 --> 01:16:20,702
Connection's reestablishing.
You'll have signal in three, two, one.

870
01:16:20,785 --> 01:16:22,454
All right, shut him down.

871
01:16:26,249 --> 01:16:27,751
Done.

872
01:16:27,834 --> 01:16:31,129
WOMAN: Power systems online.
MAN: Full control established.

873
01:16:31,212 --> 01:16:32,922
HARTING:
All right. Where are you going?

874
01:16:33,006 --> 01:16:36,342
- You know where. Wigans?
- No chance. I need you on Wigans.

875
01:16:36,426 --> 01:16:38,970
He clearly knows too much.
I need him out of the picture.

876
01:16:39,053 --> 01:16:42,307
No. You get your hands dirty this time.

877
01:16:44,684 --> 01:16:45,685
[CLICKS]

878
01:16:50,440 --> 01:16:52,817
[♪♪♪]

879
01:16:54,986 --> 01:16:57,864
You'll remember
that I don't need to ask you.

880
01:16:58,990 --> 01:17:00,450
I do it out of respect.

881
01:17:04,078 --> 01:17:06,206
And that respect needs to be reciprocated.

882
01:17:08,333 --> 01:17:09,250
[BEEPS]

883
01:17:09,334 --> 01:17:11,044
[GASPING]

884
01:17:16,257 --> 01:17:17,091
Good girl.

885
01:17:37,904 --> 01:17:40,740
ERIC [ON RADIO]:
<i>Wigans has been holed up at the Monteverde.</i>

886
01:17:40,824 --> 01:17:44,202
<i>He's ordered $812 of room service</i>

887
01:17:44,285 --> 01:17:47,372
<i>and has watched 17 hours
of something called</i> Ladies...

888
01:17:47,455 --> 01:17:49,791
KT: Not helpful, Eric.
<i>- Sorry, yeah. Okay.</i>

889
01:17:49,874 --> 01:17:52,126
<i>He's got a six-man security detail,</i>

890
01:17:52,210 --> 01:17:56,381
<i>four in the cars
and two escorting him out the back entrance.</i>

891
01:18:09,394 --> 01:18:11,521
Excuse me. Do you have a lighter?

892
01:18:11,604 --> 01:18:14,190
MAN:
Sir, we should really get you in the car.

893
01:18:15,859 --> 01:18:17,443
A gentleman abides.

894
01:18:17,527 --> 01:18:19,320
- Allow me.
- Thank you.

895
01:18:26,870 --> 01:18:28,288
The name's Wigans.

896
01:18:30,665 --> 01:18:32,292
Wilfred...

897
01:18:32,375 --> 01:18:34,168
[COUGHING]

898
01:18:34,252 --> 01:18:35,837
Yeah.

899
01:18:38,464 --> 01:18:40,300
It's not good for you.

900
01:19:19,464 --> 01:19:20,590
HARTING [DISTORTED]:
Garrison.

901
01:19:20,673 --> 01:19:22,383
Garrison.

902
01:19:23,676 --> 01:19:25,470
You.

903
01:19:28,473 --> 01:19:29,891
What is this place?

904
01:19:29,974 --> 01:19:32,268
This is a neural space,

905
01:19:32,352 --> 01:19:35,104
where we can talk in private.

906
01:19:36,356 --> 01:19:38,191
Let me make this easier.

907
01:19:41,194 --> 01:19:43,196
[♪♪♪]

908
01:20:12,475 --> 01:20:14,394
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
This is all for you.

909
01:20:17,063 --> 01:20:18,398
You used me.

910
01:20:19,524 --> 01:20:20,566
You made me kill.

911
01:20:20,650 --> 01:20:23,611
I didn't make you kill, Ray.
You've always done that.

912
01:20:23,695 --> 01:20:26,155
I just cleared the path.
I freed you to be your best.

913
01:20:26,239 --> 01:20:27,615
- My best?!
- Yes.

914
01:20:28,658 --> 01:20:33,204
By making me watch them kill my wife
over and over and over again?

915
01:20:33,287 --> 01:20:37,625
Revenge is what makes
a man like you exceptional, Ray.

916
01:20:37,709 --> 01:20:39,711
You know nothing about men like me!

917
01:20:39,794 --> 01:20:41,713
You sure about that?

918
01:20:41,796 --> 01:20:45,341
You chose war because you love it.
That's who you are.

919
01:20:46,426 --> 01:20:47,677
You don't know what I love.

920
01:20:49,178 --> 01:20:51,389
Or why I did what I did.

921
01:20:52,557 --> 01:20:56,019
People like you break people like me
into pieces.

922
01:20:56,102 --> 01:20:57,812
And you put us into these little boxes

923
01:20:57,895 --> 01:21:00,440
so you can understand us
and you can control us.

924
01:21:00,523 --> 01:21:01,858
But you can't control us.

925
01:21:01,941 --> 01:21:03,818
People like boxes, Ray.

926
01:21:03,901 --> 01:21:07,655
They need structure. They need guidance.
That's just a reality.

927
01:21:07,739 --> 01:21:11,117
Says the man
who puts the shadows on the wall.

928
01:21:13,244 --> 01:21:15,079
There's nothing left for you out there.

929
01:21:16,122 --> 01:21:20,084
Nothing. In here,
you get to be the best version of yourself.

930
01:21:20,168 --> 01:21:22,128
You rescue the hostage.

931
01:21:22,211 --> 01:21:25,423
You get to spend the night
with a woman who loves you.

932
01:21:25,506 --> 01:21:28,885
And you wake up in the morning
with a new body and a defined purpose.

933
01:21:28,968 --> 01:21:30,720
What more could you ask for?

934
01:21:30,803 --> 01:21:32,764
Your best version of me!

935
01:21:32,847 --> 01:21:34,682
Not mine!

936
01:21:37,060 --> 01:21:39,270
Don't you get it?

937
01:21:40,688 --> 01:21:44,984
- Life is about not knowing what's coming.
- What, like when it's taken away from you?

938
01:21:46,235 --> 01:21:50,364
Not knowing when it's gonna be taken away
from you, is that what you mean, Ray?

939
01:21:53,326 --> 01:21:55,536
You did this to me.

940
01:21:55,620 --> 01:21:57,246
You made me.

941
01:21:58,247 --> 01:22:00,750
But you can't control me forever.

942
01:22:00,833 --> 01:22:03,920
I will find you, and I will end...

943
01:22:05,797 --> 01:22:06,631
No, you won't.

944
01:22:18,893 --> 01:22:20,228
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

945
01:22:23,439 --> 01:22:25,691
DALTON:
Just in time to say goodbye.

946
01:22:29,904 --> 01:22:31,572
He's back?

947
01:22:32,573 --> 01:22:34,200
For the time being.

948
01:22:34,283 --> 01:22:36,244
Harting's pulling the nanites?

949
01:22:39,247 --> 01:22:41,165
On the table now.

950
01:22:46,796 --> 01:22:48,506
[♪♪♪]

951
01:22:54,345 --> 01:22:56,514
Show's about to start.

952
01:23:07,275 --> 01:23:08,276
Wigans got away.

953
01:23:08,359 --> 01:23:10,611
- What?
- He knew I was coming.

954
01:23:10,695 --> 01:23:13,614
Eric was sloppy tracking him down.

955
01:23:16,117 --> 01:23:17,827
HARTING:
Okay, stop the extraction.

956
01:23:17,910 --> 01:23:21,539
Prep the sim.
Rebuild the target package for Wigans.

957
01:23:28,045 --> 01:23:30,047
- One more run.
- Again?

958
01:23:31,549 --> 01:23:33,426
Yes, again.

959
01:23:33,509 --> 01:23:36,762
I wouldn't have to send him after Wigans
if you had done your job.

960
01:23:44,520 --> 01:23:46,189
Do it quickly.

961
01:23:53,654 --> 01:23:56,449
Okay, start the sequence.
We'll alter it real-time.

962
01:24:01,495 --> 01:24:04,248
MAN 1 [ON RADIO]:
<i>No sign of alpha target. Moving location.</i>

963
01:24:07,251 --> 01:24:09,128
[ALARM BLARES]

964
01:24:14,800 --> 01:24:16,093
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

965
01:24:22,683 --> 01:24:25,019
[MACHINE WHIRRING]

966
01:24:26,604 --> 01:24:29,232
Okay. That should do it.

967
01:24:29,315 --> 01:24:30,900
It's not my best work, but...

968
01:24:30,983 --> 01:24:32,944
Is it ever?

969
01:24:41,577 --> 01:24:42,536
Ray?

970
01:24:42,620 --> 01:24:43,829
[COMPUTER BEEPING]

971
01:24:45,248 --> 01:24:47,625
He's peaking way too early. Why is that?

972
01:24:47,708 --> 01:24:51,212
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
His vitals are all over the place.

973
01:24:52,922 --> 01:24:54,298
Pull... Pull that up.

974
01:24:54,382 --> 01:24:55,883
Why is this happening?

975
01:24:56,884 --> 01:24:58,511
Someone's altering the sim.

976
01:24:58,594 --> 01:25:00,805
Well, who is altering it?!

977
01:25:03,933 --> 01:25:05,268
KT.

978
01:25:06,310 --> 01:25:10,022
Call Tibbs and Dalton to command.
Armed. And fix that sim!

979
01:25:15,236 --> 01:25:17,655
All right, I got this, I got this. Come on.

980
01:25:20,074 --> 01:25:21,575
I know you.

981
01:25:22,618 --> 01:25:23,452
KT.

982
01:25:24,954 --> 01:25:26,831
HARTING:
KT, open the door.

983
01:25:27,790 --> 01:25:30,626
KT, what are you doing here?

984
01:25:31,627 --> 01:25:34,297
What I should have done a long time ago.

985
01:25:41,470 --> 01:25:42,847
[BEEPING]

986
01:25:44,265 --> 01:25:46,559
I'm in. I'm in.

987
01:25:47,518 --> 01:25:48,602
[STOOL CLATTERS]

988
01:25:48,686 --> 01:25:50,563
Son of a virgin.

989
01:25:52,231 --> 01:25:53,566
Okay.

990
01:25:53,649 --> 01:25:54,692
[CHUCKLES]

991
01:26:00,948 --> 01:26:04,702
You thought you could lock
old Wigans out of his own code?

992
01:26:06,579 --> 01:26:08,998
[♪♪♪]

993
01:26:13,711 --> 01:26:16,964
Wait. Wait, what?
What the hell is happening?

994
01:26:17,048 --> 01:26:18,049
No, no, no.

995
01:26:18,132 --> 01:26:19,884
[ALARM BEEPING]

996
01:26:19,967 --> 01:26:22,470
How...? How is she doing this?

997
01:26:25,639 --> 01:26:27,350
What? Heh.

998
01:26:27,433 --> 01:26:29,393
-I said, drop your gun!
ERIC: You got this.

999
01:26:29,477 --> 01:26:31,020
[GROWLS]

1000
01:26:31,729 --> 01:26:35,608
Okay, my son,
if you're gonna come for the king,

1001
01:26:35,691 --> 01:26:37,902
you'd best not miss.

1002
01:26:38,903 --> 01:26:40,946
HARTING:
KT! Open this goddamn door!

1003
01:26:41,030 --> 01:26:44,950
That should do it. Pow, pow, pow.

1004
01:26:45,034 --> 01:26:47,411
Pow, pow, pow.

1005
01:26:51,248 --> 01:26:53,667
Um... Okay.

1006
01:27:01,967 --> 01:27:03,344
Oh, Jesus.

1007
01:27:03,427 --> 01:27:04,553
[CHUCKLES]

1008
01:27:14,105 --> 01:27:16,107
[♪♪♪]

1009
01:27:19,026 --> 01:27:20,194
Oh, Jesus.

1010
01:27:21,237 --> 01:27:23,239
Twenty quid he just said, "Oh, Jesus."

1011
01:27:23,322 --> 01:27:25,032
Twenty quid...

1012
01:27:26,033 --> 01:27:28,786
I need real friends! Or a therapist.

1013
01:27:37,294 --> 01:27:38,129
[DOOR OPENS]

1014
01:27:38,212 --> 01:27:41,173
- Why are you doing this?
- Because he deserves the truth.

1015
01:27:42,216 --> 01:27:44,677
The truth is, nobody wants
to make real decisions anymore.

1016
01:27:49,765 --> 01:27:52,351
They just wanna feel like they have.

1017
01:27:54,937 --> 01:27:57,022
Goodbye, KT.

1018
01:27:58,149 --> 01:28:00,526
Like I would let you do that again.

1019
01:28:01,193 --> 01:28:02,194
[DEVICE BEEPING]

1020
01:28:10,828 --> 01:28:11,912
[COUGHS]

1021
01:28:15,166 --> 01:28:18,169
HARTING [ON RADIO]: <i>KT's gone rogue.
Garrison is awake and offline.</i>

1022
01:28:18,252 --> 01:28:21,130
<i>Find him and shut him down.
Kill him if you have to.</i>

1023
01:28:22,882 --> 01:28:25,217
[♪♪♪]

1024
01:28:54,997 --> 01:28:55,831
[BEEPING]

1025
01:29:00,669 --> 01:29:02,588
Headed to the 74th floor.

1026
01:29:04,423 --> 01:29:07,676
WIGANS: <i>Morning, sunshine. Remember me?</i>
- Wigans.

1027
01:29:07,760 --> 01:29:11,222
[IN DEEP VOICE] "No, it is I,
King Jaffe Joffer, ruler of Zamunda."

1028
01:29:11,305 --> 01:29:13,724
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Of course it's Wigans. Who else would it be?

1029
01:29:13,807 --> 01:29:17,645
Listen, mate, uh,
I'm sending you coordinates to my van.

1030
01:29:17,728 --> 01:29:20,397
I realize that sounded a lot creepier
than I meant it.

1031
01:29:20,481 --> 01:29:22,274
RAY:
I've got unfinished business.

1032
01:29:22,358 --> 01:29:23,651
Oh, great.

1033
01:29:24,652 --> 01:29:27,988
-Wait. Come again.
KT: <i>Wigans, where's Garrison?</i>

1034
01:29:28,072 --> 01:29:30,491
I don't know.
Apparently, doing whatever he wants.

1035
01:29:30,574 --> 01:29:34,119
<i>It's about time. Phase two.
Coming up on the server room.</i>

1036
01:29:34,203 --> 01:29:36,121
Okay, there you are.

1037
01:29:37,831 --> 01:29:42,044
Which means it's time for me
to walk you through a low-level data erase.

1038
01:29:42,127 --> 01:29:45,548
Now, obviously, I've got about 1000 years
of coding experience.

1039
01:29:45,631 --> 01:29:48,300
<i>I'm literally a genius.
You're so very welcome.</i>

1040
01:29:48,384 --> 01:29:51,095
So it is vital you do exactly
what it is I tell you.

1041
01:29:51,178 --> 01:29:53,389
<i>Step one. Find the sysop terminal.</i>

1042
01:29:53,472 --> 01:29:55,474
<i>It should be somewhere near...</i>

1043
01:29:55,558 --> 01:29:57,393
[♪♪♪]

1044
01:30:37,933 --> 01:30:39,184
<i>Step 36.</i>

1045
01:30:39,268 --> 01:30:41,312
This one is absolutely vital.

1046
01:30:41,395 --> 01:30:43,981
Type control, command...

1047
01:30:44,064 --> 01:30:46,066
[ALARM BEEPING]

1048
01:30:47,234 --> 01:30:48,110
What the...?

1049
01:30:52,406 --> 01:30:55,909
- I thought I'd do it the old-fashioned way.
- Oh, really?

1050
01:30:55,993 --> 01:30:59,913
It's good to know
literally no one is listening to me.

1051
01:30:59,997 --> 01:31:01,874
Why didn't I think of that?

1052
01:31:01,957 --> 01:31:04,585
Control, command, "burn the building down."

1053
01:31:04,668 --> 01:31:06,629
Kobe!

1054
01:31:07,379 --> 01:31:10,007
[♪♪♪]

1055
01:31:31,528 --> 01:31:32,571
Yeah.

1056
01:31:32,655 --> 01:31:34,698
That one was my idea.

1057
01:32:23,205 --> 01:32:25,457
Right behind you. Dropping in!

1058
01:32:52,067 --> 01:32:54,945
DALTON:
On my way. Keep him busy!

1059
01:33:00,826 --> 01:33:02,119
RAY:
Let it go, Tibbs.

1060
01:33:02,202 --> 01:33:05,456
DALTON:
I'll be on you in three, two... Get clear!

1061
01:33:13,088 --> 01:33:14,006
Ungh!

1062
01:33:14,089 --> 01:33:16,216
DALTON:
Let's see him survive that.

1063
01:33:20,888 --> 01:33:24,725
Oh, goddamn it.
This guy just won't fucking die.

1064
01:33:38,447 --> 01:33:40,073
Hang on, Tibbs!

1065
01:33:42,951 --> 01:33:44,411
TIBBS:
No!

1066
01:33:57,716 --> 01:33:59,718
[♪♪♪]

1067
01:34:15,901 --> 01:34:18,111
TIBBS:
Dalton! What are you doing? Help me!

1068
01:34:19,488 --> 01:34:20,739
Dalton!

1069
01:34:22,658 --> 01:34:24,660
[SCREAMING]

1070
01:34:25,410 --> 01:34:27,329
DALTON:
I did say hang on!

1071
01:35:22,593 --> 01:35:24,595
[POWER WHIRRING DOWN]

1072
01:35:26,680 --> 01:35:28,807
No, no, no. Oh, no. Oh, shit.

1073
01:35:31,310 --> 01:35:34,521
-Oh, that's not good.
KT: <i>What the hell was that?</i>

1074
01:35:34,605 --> 01:35:36,857
- It felt like a bomb went off.
- Oh, bloody hell.

1075
01:35:36,940 --> 01:35:40,152
Yeah. It's a... It's a problem.

1076
01:35:40,235 --> 01:35:43,780
HARTING: Go. Go, go, go. Come on.
Start the car. We're leaving.

1077
01:35:44,907 --> 01:35:46,992
RAY:
Harting!

1078
01:35:49,995 --> 01:35:51,496
HARTING:
Goddamn it.

1079
01:35:57,002 --> 01:35:58,670
Talk to me, Wigans. Where's Garrison?

1080
01:35:58,754 --> 01:36:02,424
Hang on. Ground floor,
east side, headed for Harting.

1081
01:36:04,593 --> 01:36:06,845
You just don't get it, do you?

1082
01:36:06,929 --> 01:36:08,472
I can rebuild all of this.

1083
01:36:11,558 --> 01:36:14,394
And I am the only one who can rebuild you.

1084
01:36:15,437 --> 01:36:17,856
You cannot survive without me.

1085
01:36:17,940 --> 01:36:19,942
[♪♪♪]

1086
01:36:40,837 --> 01:36:42,297
Okay, fine.

1087
01:36:49,972 --> 01:36:50,806
[ALARM BEEPING]

1088
01:36:50,889 --> 01:36:53,100
Holy shit. Oh, no.

1089
01:36:53,183 --> 01:36:56,019
Bloody hell. Um, uh, mate?

1090
01:36:56,103 --> 01:36:57,771
What are you doing? You have to stop.

1091
01:37:11,952 --> 01:37:13,954
KT, he's almost down to nothing.

1092
01:37:14,037 --> 01:37:16,790
- That's impossible.
<i>- He's overclocking the nanites.</i>

1093
01:37:16,873 --> 01:37:20,669
If he doesn't stop,
I won't be able to bring him back.

1094
01:37:20,752 --> 01:37:22,212
Shit!

1095
01:37:22,295 --> 01:37:24,297
[♪♪♪]

1096
01:37:28,510 --> 01:37:30,012
[DEVICE BEEPING]

1097
01:37:38,603 --> 01:37:40,564
Don't make me do this.

1098
01:37:57,122 --> 01:37:59,750
[DISTORTED]
I told you I'd find you.

1099
01:38:03,628 --> 01:38:06,673
Oh, man. He's done.

1100
01:38:06,757 --> 01:38:08,675
It's over, KT.

1101
01:38:11,344 --> 01:38:14,765
Yes, you did.
But all that's now left is Ray Garrison.

1102
01:38:15,974 --> 01:38:17,476
And that's enough.

1103
01:38:39,498 --> 01:38:42,417
KT: <i>How much longer, Wigans?</i>
WIGANS: <i>Don't, don't, don't rush me.</i>

1104
01:38:42,501 --> 01:38:45,087
KT: <i>Is this going to work?</i>
WIGANS: <i>It always works.</i>

1105
01:38:45,170 --> 01:38:49,758
<i>Well, it did last time. All right,
A over B reattached. There we go.</i>

1106
01:38:49,841 --> 01:38:52,010
KT: <i>Should you be eating
while you're doing that?</i>

1107
01:38:52,094 --> 01:38:54,096
WIGANS:
<i>Yeah. There we go.</i>

1108
01:38:54,179 --> 01:38:56,098
KT:
<i>It's okay. It's okay. We've got you.</i>

1109
01:38:57,557 --> 01:38:59,518
WIGANS:
Are you all right?

1110
01:39:00,519 --> 01:39:02,312
Are you with me?

1111
01:39:04,272 --> 01:39:06,233
Take it easy.

1112
01:39:06,316 --> 01:39:08,193
Where am I?

1113
01:39:10,195 --> 01:39:11,446
WIGANS:
Relax.

1114
01:39:12,531 --> 01:39:15,158
Relax. Take it easy.

1115
01:39:16,535 --> 01:39:19,329
No car batteries this time.

1116
01:39:21,623 --> 01:39:24,167
It's good to see you, man. How you feeling?

1117
01:39:34,928 --> 01:39:36,972
It's good to see you, Wigans.

1118
01:39:37,681 --> 01:39:39,683
[♪♪♪]

1119
01:39:42,102 --> 01:39:46,523
You don't know how glad I am to hear that.
I wasn't sure you'd remember anything.

1120
01:39:46,606 --> 01:39:49,734
I thought you were gonna wake up
like a gorilla in a cage and rip me apart.

1121
01:39:49,818 --> 01:39:52,654
That is absolutely fantastic.

1122
01:39:52,737 --> 01:39:56,366
But what you probably don't remember
is that I also made some adjustments

1123
01:39:56,449 --> 01:39:58,493
to increase your stamina.

1124
01:39:58,577 --> 01:40:01,580
You know, your stamina?
I don't know why I done that.

1125
01:40:01,663 --> 01:40:04,499
But what I mean is, you don't
gotta keep refilling the gas tank.

1126
01:40:04,583 --> 01:40:06,042
Not at all.

1127
01:40:06,126 --> 01:40:07,377
Get what I mean?

1128
01:40:07,460 --> 01:40:11,214
If you were a three before,
you're now an 18. Heh-heh. And I done that.

1129
01:40:11,298 --> 01:40:14,217
Well, we did.

1130
01:40:14,301 --> 01:40:15,760
We.

1131
01:40:15,844 --> 01:40:16,928
[SNAPS FINGERS]

1132
01:40:17,012 --> 01:40:18,805
We.

1133
01:40:20,807 --> 01:40:26,688
He's awake, and he remembers everything.
Hopefully not everything-everything.

1134
01:40:26,771 --> 01:40:30,108
You know, because if you recall, KT,
how we found him,

1135
01:40:30,192 --> 01:40:33,236
his face was smooshed up against his own...

1136
01:40:33,320 --> 01:40:34,529
[WIGANS CHUCKLES]

1137
01:40:35,822 --> 01:40:37,657
Thank you, Wigans.

1138
01:40:37,741 --> 01:40:38,783
Yeah.

1139
01:40:41,912 --> 01:40:43,455
You're welcome.

1140
01:40:52,672 --> 01:40:55,300
KT:
It's beautiful, isn't it?

1141
01:40:55,383 --> 01:40:58,094
RAY: It's like a dream.
- It is.

1142
01:41:08,063 --> 01:41:08,939
- Ray, I...
- Don't.

1143
01:41:10,148 --> 01:41:11,483
You don't have to.

1144
01:41:12,984 --> 01:41:15,237
Who we were, what we did?

1145
01:41:16,363 --> 01:41:17,989
That was the past.

1146
01:41:18,990 --> 01:41:23,036
You know, Harting was wrong
about a lot of it, but, uh...

1147
01:41:23,119 --> 01:41:24,663
he did get one thing right.

1148
01:41:26,748 --> 01:41:29,793
Who we were doesn't have to define
who we're gonna be.

1149
01:41:31,378 --> 01:41:33,922
We can choose. We all can.

1150
01:41:53,858 --> 01:41:55,860
[♪♪♪]

1151
01:42:17,007 --> 01:42:19,217
So where to now?

1152
01:42:19,301 --> 01:42:20,593
KT:
I have no idea.

1153
01:42:20,677 --> 01:42:21,720
[ENGINE STARTS]

1154
01:42:23,096 --> 01:42:24,139
Perfect.

1155
01:42:29,686 --> 01:42:32,105
WIGANS [ON RADIO]:
<i>A little too perfect, if you ask me.</i>

1156
01:42:32,188 --> 01:42:34,065
<i>Are you serious?</i>

1157
01:42:34,149 --> 01:42:36,735
<i>Ride into the sunset?
Are we sure this ain't all a simu...?</i>

1158
01:42:36,818 --> 01:42:38,820
[♪♪♪]

1159
01:44:11,496 --> 01:44:13,498
[♪♪♪]

